OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1773745530
OL,3,CTwo dead after outbreak of 'invasive'
OL,4,Cdisease reported at university
OL,6,FIt is an uncommon but serious disease
OL,7,Fcaused by meningococcal bacteria.
OL,9,FThose affected are believed to be
OL,10,Fstudents at the university, and all
OL,11,Fcases have been reported between
OL,12,FFriday (13 March) and Sunday (15
OL,13,FMarch).
OL,15,FThe UK Health Security Agency and the
OL,16,FNHS are now arranging antibiotics for
OL,17,Fsome students at the University of
OL,18,FKent following the incident.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1773745530
OL,3,CTwo dead after outbreak of 'invasive'
OL,4,Cdisease reported at university
OL,6,FSymptoms of meningitis include
OL,7,Fsymptoms such as headache, fever and a
OL,8,Fstiff neck. Anyone who feels unwell,
OL,9,For believes they may have the disease,
OL,10,Fshould call 111, health bosses said.
OL,12,FPeople should also check in on friends
OL,13,Fwho are unwell. Taking action, the
OL,14,FUKHSA says, is vital, and "could save
OL,15,Ftheir life".
OL,17,FThe University of Kent told ITV
OL,18,FMeridian that it is working with the
OL,19,FNHS and UKHSA to ensure staff and
OL,20,Fstudents are informed of the situation.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1773745530
OL,3,CTwo dead after outbreak of 'invasive'
OL,4,Cdisease reported at university
OL,6,FThe UKHSA says that "very
OL,7,Foccasionally" meningococcal bacteria
OL,8,Fcan cause serious illness, including
OL,9,Finflammation of the lining of the
OL,10,Fbrain and blood poisoning, which can
OL,11,Frapidly lead to sepsis.
OL,13,FTrish Mannes, UKHSA regional deputy
OL,14,Fdirector for the South East, said: "We
OL,15,Funderstand that many people at the
OL,16,Funiversity and in the wider community
OL,17,Fwill be affected by this sad news and
OL,18,Fwe would like to offer our condolences
OL,19,Fto the friends and family involved.
OL,26,@nD@UOUoD@MO]vD@dOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1773745530
OL,3,CTwo dead after outbreak of 'invasive'
OL,4,Cdisease reported at university
OL,6,F"Students and staff will
OL,7,Funderstandably be feeling worried
OL,8,Fabout the risk of further cases;
OL,9,Fhowever, we would like to reassure
OL,10,Fthem that close contacts of cases have
OL,11,Fbeen given antibiotics as a
OL,12,Fprecautionary measure.
OL,14,F"Advice and support is being offered
OL,15,Fto the wider student community, and to
OL,16,Flocal hospitals and NHS 111, and we're
OL,17,Fmonitoring the situation closely.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1773745530
OL,3,CTwo dead after outbreak of 'invasive'
OL,4,Cdisease reported at university
OL,6,F"Meningococcal disease can progress
OL,7,Frapidly, so it's essential that
OL,8,Fstudents and staff are alert to the
OL,9,Fsigns and symptoms of meningococcal
OL,10,Fmeningitis and septicaemia, which can
OL,11,Finclude a fever, headache, rapid
OL,12,Fbreathing, drowsiness, shivering,
OL,13,Fvomiting and cold hands and feet.
OL,14,FSepticaemia can also cause a
OL,15,Fcharacteristic rash that does not fade
OL,16,Fwhen pressed against a glass.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1773745530
OL,3,CTwo dead after outbreak of 'invasive'
OL,4,Cdisease reported at university
OL,6,F"Students are particularly at risk of
OL,7,Fmissing the early warning signs of
OL,8,Fmeningitis because they can be easily
OL,9,Fconfused with other illnesses such as
OL,10,Fa bad cold, flu or even a hangover.
OL,12,F"That's why it's vital that, if a
OL,13,Ffriend goes to bed unwell, you check
OL,14,Fon them regularly and don't hesitate
OL,15,Fto seek medical help by contacting
OL,16,Ftheir GP or calling NHS 111 if they
OL,17,Fhave these symptoms or you're
OL,18,Fconcerned about them. This could save
OL,19,Ftheir life."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU{D@LO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/8
